[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White tries to live with expanding his living shape at 1, however it is a greedy idea.
\par Black 2 is the vital point for breaking the eye.
\par
\par After White 3, Black 4 another good move, and it becomes the \cf1\b dead\cf0\b0  \cf2\b five space shape\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par If White plays at 4 instead of 3, Black takes with A and White is still dead.
\par
