Dia. 03 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's attachment at 1 is the vital point for living. It is also the famous \cf1\b 1-2 point\cf0\b0 .
\par Black 2 is the strongest resistance, but White 3 is a good move.
\par
\par If Black plays at A, White can live with B.
\par In actual game, Black plays at 3 instead of 2 and White lives with 2.
\par }
